# Soft & Chewy Chocolate Snickerdoodles

Based on [https://sallysbakingaddiction.com/chocolate-snickerdoodles](https://sallysbakingaddiction.com/chocolate-snickerdoodles)

{ rating=0 image="None" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

### Cookies

- [ ] 2.67 cups all-purpose flour, spooned & leveled
- [ ] 1/2 cup unsweetened natural cocoa powder
- [ ] 1 tsp cream of tartar
- [ ] 1 tsp baking soda
- [ ] 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon
- [ ] 1/2 tsp salt
- [ ] 1 cup (16 Tbsps) unsalted butter, softened
- [ ] 1 cup granulated sugar
- [ ] 1/2 cup packed light or dark brown sugar
- [ ] 2 large eggs, room temperature
- [ ] 1 tsp pure vanilla extract

### Topping

- [ ] 1/3 cup granulated sugar
- [ ] 1 tsp ground cinnamon

## Recipe

1. Whisk together flour, cocoa powder, cream of tartar, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt; set aside.
1. Beat butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar until creamy (about 3 minutes). Add eggs and vanilla; beat until combined.
1. Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients; beat on low speed until incorporated.
1. Cover and chill dough at least 2 hours (or up to 3 days). If chilling longer, let sit 20 minutes at room temperature before scooping.
1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Line baking sheets with parchment paper.
1. Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon for topping.
1. Scoop dough into 1.5 Tbsp (35g) balls; roll in cinnamon-sugar. Arrange 2-3 inches apart on baking sheets.
1. Bake until edges are set but centers look puffy (13-15 minutes). Cool on sheet 10 minutes, then transfer to cooling rack.

## Notes

- Cream of tartar provides signature tang and soft texture—not recommended to omit
- Cookies will slightly deflate as they cool
- For crackly tops: ensure well-chilled dough and proper bake time so cookies puff in the oven
- Store in airtight container at room temperature for up to 5 days
